 # Changelog
 
+## 2026-07-16 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S1-P02-T012 (unified Source Registry schema)
+
+- Twelfth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program and the first of S1-P02 (Source Registry single source truth), one task per run. Goal: cover the existing five boards and China A0-A2 and distinguish official evidence from discovery. NOT_DEPLOYED, 0 recurring cloud cost; no crawl behaviour, worker, or D1 changed (schema-only). Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/: schemas/source_registry.schema.json (draft-07: source identity with a unique source_id, the authority enum china_official/intl_official/journal/preprint/media/search/aggregator, an authority_level restricted to A0/A1/A2 for china_official, official_evidence, and enable/health/cursor fields enabled/health_status/cursor/cadence, with conditional rules), tools/validate_source_registry.py, and source_registry.sample.json (7 sources across the five boards + China A0/A1/A2 + a discovery aggregator/media). Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S1-P02-T012/test-results/registry_schema_tests.txt): the valid sample is VALID; a china_official source with authority_level A3 is INVALID and one missing the level is INVALID (China official levels outside A0/A1/A2 fail); a media source marked official_evidence=true is INVALID (media can never be official evidence); and a duplicate source_id is INVALID. This is the schema base for DRIFT-FACT-006 (source-truth drift); the actual migration of live sources is T013 and the compiler is T014. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
+
 ## 2026-07-16 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S1-P01-T011 (generated status + drift check; DRIFT-FACT-007 resolved)
 
 - Eleventh task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program (S1-P01), one task per run. Goal: eliminate the STATUS contradiction where docs/v03/STATUS.yaml simultaneously claimed cloud-native (J5) and Tunnel/Mac-mirror (R6) as current -- DRIFT-FACT-007. NOT_DEPLOYED, 0 recurring cloud cost; the worker/D1/production untouched. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/: STATUS_GENERATED.md (machine-generated current deployment status -- cloud-native adp-cloud Worker + D1 + cron, NO Cloudflare Tunnel, NO Mac 127.0.0.1 mirror, NO LaunchAgent residents; build_id bd67a78020a3 from the live /build.json, commit/cron/schema/registry/content_hash from the deployment manifest), tools/generate_status.py (generator), tools/check_status_drift.py (CI drift check). The stale section is archived by marking docs/v03/STATUS.yaml R6 superseded_by J5_cloud_native with a superseded_note pointing at STATUS_GENERATED.md. Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S1-P01-T011/test-results/status_drift_check.txt): check_status_drift = PASS (generated status matches the manifest commit/cron/registry/content_hash and asserts tunnel/Mac retired; R6 is superseded); a negative test that removes R6's superseded_by makes the check return DRIFT (exit 1), proving a hand-written old architecture cannot silently override the generated current; restoring it returns PASS; and STATUS.yaml still parses. The generated status's build_id equals the live /build.json (docs consistent with the build endpoint). S1 value: single-truth deployment status. Cost: generate_status optionally pulls /build.json once at generation, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
